public class CsvLine extends com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.language.collections.list.StringList implements com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.language.reflection.property.PropertyValueSource, com.telenav.kivakit.kernel.messaging.repeaters.RepeaterMixin
A model of a line in a CSV (Comma Separated Variable) file. CsvLine objects are produced by CsvReader and consumed by CsvWriter.

Properties

This model has a line number available with lineNumber() and it conforms to a CsvSchema, available with schema(). Columns are separated in the CSV file with a delimiter character, normally a comma, that is passed to the constructor CsvLine(CsvSchema, char). Values from the line can be retrieved by column with get(CsvColumn) and they can be provided with set(CsvColumn, Object).

Converting a Line to an Object

A CsvLine can be converted directly to an object with populatedObject(Class). A new instance of the class is created and its properties are populated using the CsvSchema of this line. For details, see populatedObject(Class) and valueFor(Property).

Author:
jonathanl (shibo)

    • populatedObject

      public <T> T populatedObject​(Class<T> type)
      Returns:
      An object of the given type with its properties populated by ObjectPopulator using CsvPropertyFilter. Properties of the object that correspond to CsvColumns using KivaKit property naming are retrieved with PropertyValueSource.valueFor(Property) (see below) and set on the new object by reflection. The result is an object corresponding to this line.
